  "local_port": 54726,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good dance club songs?",
  "response": "Creating the perfect dance club playlist involves a mix of high-energy tracks, infectious beats, and crowd-pleasing hits. Here's a list of some great dance club songs that have been popular and are sure to keep the energy high on the dance floor:\n\n### **Current Hits (2023)**\n1. **\"Dance the Night\" \u2013 Dua Lipa**\n   - Featured in the *Barbie* movie soundtrack, this track combines catchy pop melodies with a danceable beat.\n\n2. **\"Unholy\" \u2013 Sam Smith & Kim Petras**\n   - A provocative and edgy song with strong beats that's been a favorite in clubs.\n\n3. **\"Flowers\" \u2013 Miley Cyrus**\n   - An empowering pop anthem with an upbeat tempo perfect for dancing.\n\n4. **\"Calm Down\" \u2013 Rema & Selena Gomez**\n   - A blend of Afrobeats and pop that creates a vibrant dance atmosphere.\n\n5. **\"Die for You\" (Remix) \u2013 The Weeknd & Ariana Grande**\n   - A remix that adds a fresh twist to a beloved hit, enhancing its dance appeal.\n\n### **Classic Crowd-Pleasers**\n6. **\"Levitating\" \u2013 Dua Lipa ft. DaBaby**\n   - A modern classic with a disco-inspired beat that's always a hit.\n\n7. **\"Don't Start Now\" \u2013 Dua Lipa**\n   - Another Dua Lipa favorite, known for its infectious bassline and danceable rhythm.\n\n8. **\"Uptown Funk\" \u2013 Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars**\n   - A timeless track with a funk groove that gets everyone moving.\n\n9. **\"Turn Down for What\" \u2013 DJ Snake & Lil Jon**\n   - High-energy beats and intense drops make this a staple in many clubs.\n\n10. **\"Titanium\" \u2013 David Guetta ft. Sia**\n    - An empowering anthem with soaring vocals and a powerful beat.\n\n### **EDM and Electronic Favorites**\n11. **\"Closer\" \u2013 The Chainsmokers ft. Halsey**\n    - A melodic electronic track that's both catchy and dance-friendly.\n\n12. **\"Lean On\" \u2013 Major Lazer & DJ Snake ft. M\u00d8**\n    - Combines dancehall and electronic beats for a global dance sensation.\n\n13. **\"Wake Me Up\" \u2013 Avicii**\n    - A classic EDM track that never fails to energize the crowd.\n\n14. **\"Don't You Worry Child\" \u2013 Swedish House Mafia**\n    - An anthemic song with uplifting melodies perfect for big dance moments.\n\n15. **\"Blinding Lights\" \u2013 The Weeknd**\n    - While not strictly EDM, its synth-heavy beats make it a dance floor favorite.\n\n### **Hip-Hop and Pop Crossovers**\n16. **\"Savage Remix\" \u2013 Megan Thee Stallion ft. Beyonc\u00e9**\n    - A high-energy remix that blends hip-hop vibes with pop flair.\n\n17. **\"Savage Love (Laxed \u2013 Siren Beat)\" \u2013 Jawsh 685 & Jason Derulo**\n    - A catchy tune with a beat that\u2019s perfect for dancing.\n\n18. **\"Roses (Imanbek Remix)\" \u2013 SAINt JHN**\n    - A remix that transforms the original into a club-ready banger.\n\n19. **\"Bad Habits\" \u2013 Ed Sheeran**\n    - A pop track with a darker edge and a beat that keeps the momentum going.\n\n20. **\"Montero (Call Me By Your Name)\" \u2013 Lil Nas X**\n    - A bold and vibrant song that brings unique energy to the dance floor.\n\n### **Up-and-Coming Tracks**\n21. **\"Pepas\" \u2013 Farruko (David Guetta Remix)**\n    - A high-energy remix of a Latin hit that\u2019s been making waves in clubs worldwide.\n\n22. **\"Peppermint\" \u2013 The Knocks ft. Foster the People**\n    - A fresh track with an upbeat tempo that's perfect for dancing.\n\n23. **\"STAY\" \u2013 The Kid LAROI & Justin Bieber**\n    - A pop tune with an infectious beat that keeps the dance floor lively.\n\n24. **\"Industry Baby\" \u2013 Lil Nas X & Jack Harlow (Steve Aoki Remix)**\n    - This remix adds an extra layer of energy, making it a club favorite.\n\n25. **\"Kiss Me More\" \u2013 Doja Cat ft. SZA**\n    - A smooth yet upbeat track that blends pop and R&B vibes for dancing.\n\n### **Tips for a Great Dance Club Playlist**\n- **Mix Genres:** Incorporate a variety of genres like pop, EDM, hip-hop, and Latin to cater to diverse tastes.\n- **Balance Tempo:** Alternate between high-energy tracks and slightly slower beats to keep the energy balanced.\n- **Include Classics:** Throw in some well-known classics that everyone can sing and dance along to.\n- **Stay Updated:** Keep an eye on current charts and trending songs to ensure your playlist remains fresh and relevant.\n\nThese songs are sure to elevate the energy in any dance club setting. Whether you're curating a playlist for a night out or just looking to dance at home, these tracks offer a great mix of styles and vibes to keep you moving.",
